  "claim_short": "Let \\(M\\) be a finite metric space whose preserved-extreme graph has vertex set all of \\(M\\) and is 2-connected. If \\(R>\\operatorname{diam} M\\), add one new point \\(p\\) with \\(d(p,x)=R\\) for every \\(x\\in M\\). The resulting one-point extension \\(M_R=M\\cup\\{p\\}\\) is Lipschitz-free rigid.",
